  "original_title": "\u0b95\u0bcb\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe \u0b95\u0bcb \u0b95\u0bae \u0b87\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Kota Ko Kama under the control of the army",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "During this, 10 protest activists including a lawyer from the protest were arrested.",
        "Also, the protestors said that hundreds of military personnel in civilian clothes and Air Force personnel have visited the Khalimugathidal area.",
        "The security forces have announced that they should not clash with the security forces or face arrest under the Emergency Act.",
        "However, clashes broke out between security forces and protesters while controlling the crowd.",
        "All the roads around the Kota Ko Kama area have been closed to prevent the protesters from leaving the area.",
        "In this case, it is reported that operations have been carried out to remove tents and traces in Kota Ko Gama area. (a)"
      ],
